for those of you who dont already know....i wrecked my car monday, i was rounding the turn by ritas kitchen headed towards evans going 35 ...yes i was "really" going 35, my left rear tire was low on air, got loose, slid right, then back to the left, then all the way around and into a bank, doing major front end damage to the car, and bringing out both air bags....it has been heavily depated on whether or not the car will be totalled, but after long discussion with the auto knowledgeable father i have been assured the car will not be totalled and will be back into commission eventually...for the meantime, the all powerful panzer "1988 nissan pathfinder, 2 doors, 1 doorhandle, 1 tail light, all bad A" has been brought out to transport me and other necissary goods...do not fret my friends, the carwill be repaired, possibly in less than a month, and will be recommissioned for service....

"ladies and gentlemen we can rebuilt it, we have the technology,....faster, stronger, better."

im at a point in my life where i begin to question things, dont we all reach that point on occassion?

ex 1: michelle tells me she has a dream i died in a plane crash, the day before we leave for LA

ex 2: enter LA unscathed, leave with a strange confused look upon my face, wondering if Anne Frank was truly wrong when she said there is "good in all people", or if maybe, they werent people at all..

ex 3: sitting on the tram to leave disneyland, "the happiest place on earth" watch someone come within inches of death, falling off a moving tran onto the pavement, i found myself directing traffic 30 seconds later.

ex 4: walking back to the bus, seton and I notice that thousands of guests are being detoured by this "inconvenience" as the californians called it, to walk along the road, then hundereds of cars were backed up because of this.

ex 5: return home, find one of my dear friends in pain, give them empathy and wisdom from past experiences about a faulty and tattered relationship, she tells her boyfriend, argument ensues.

ex 6: Mrs Brown's research paper, i attempted to do a well written, simple paper with as few errors as possible...i recieve the worst possible grade a 50 out of 100....

after confronting these queries with my concience, God, and what slight amount of intelligence i have, i found another question as an answer for ex 5-6, Is it all worth it? Do my efforts matter, and if so, when will i see response and reap benefits? my answer lies in ex 1-4........yes..it is all worth it, the woman who fell off the tran affected thousands of guests in one hour....imagine what we can do in a life...in the entire 5 day span i was in los angeles, the city of angels, at no point did i think of confronting these people, they were possibly the most poorly mannered people i have met, and yet i can help but ponder the possibilities, for those who are lost are always looking for the path...if los angeles were the city of angles, imagine the walk back to the bus that night.....imagine thousands exiting disney world, praying for the woman who was injured, the singing praises all the way to their cars thanking him for safety in their travels....imagine if the woman with the two boys who was complaining over a 5 minute walk after a 10 hour walk around an amusement park instead was compelled to stay with the caretakers and suport them, .......imagine if we were the same, imagine if every eff you, GD, sh**, DA, B*tch, were instead, god bless you, have a great day, praise God, God loves you, comin to church tonight? etc......the people at the drug assembly today reminded me of todays church....walk in, praise God, walk out, praise gods....

It will all be worth it in the end.

you open your mouth and before you can speak i hit the floor,

its amazing how you can do too little by trying too hard,

you seem sincere, but your eyes they decieve,

and in these tense moments you fail to notice me.

 

the smile has now left your face,

and a liars grin now sits in its place,

and i know you say you miss me,

but your still with him.

 

your still all i love but nothing that i need,

and the moment you cease to care is the moment i start to believe,

 

you open you mouth and before you speak i hit the floor,

its amazing wat you do to me when you dont try at all,

a breath spurs a million memories i try so hard to forget,

and in this moment i notice from you a sigh of regret.

 

and as the tears streak down your face,

and the smirk is now replaced with words

"i still love you"

but your still  with him.

 

i know your all that i love, and nothing that i need,

but the moment that you stop to think is the moment that i leave.

yes, i am posting again, alot is going on in my life ladies and gentlemen, and im not so sure i like it. im used to the slow relaxed easy to enjoy life a teenager should have. recently my life has gotten hectic, not in a worldly sense of course this is strictly spiritual, but i am afraid it has ran over to all walks of life. i am now in what i believe is a critical point in my youth where i must decide what i truly believe to be real and what is simply a masquarade i float through everyday. i amfraid of what i may become if i go down one road and afraid to take the first step down the other...but ihave seen a light at the end of the tunnel recently..i believe there is hope..i know there is hope..its just whether or not the hope will recognize thats what it is..or they are.. watever the case may be, i know what i want..i know what i need and i am now going to find the space between the two and move towards redemption and hopefully a better, more tolerable, more Godly, more perfect Grant, because what i am now is not what i want to be in the future..and i hate the thought of being something insufficient to even myself...therefore to sum all of my hearts thoughts and my brains contemplations, i need prayer, i need direction, and most of all, i need God

hello friends, i am enjoying life, i have found recently that it is more useful to enjoy life as it comes, and thank God for what you are given, than to blame him and sulk over what you lack,

 

p.s. chick k and guy g are now a happy couple, times are good, times are good......
